Being trans and just existing is an act of resistance 🏳️‍⚧️

Today at work, I decided to wear this T-shirt in support of trans kids. Trans youth are being ATTACKED by legislations each day and it must be talked about more. Some states even want to ban gender affirming care for EVERYONE no matter their age. Where is the uproar!???? Where are our Allies??? From my side, all I see is silence. Why aren’t people talking about this more?

We live in a scary time and I’m so tired of fighting but we need to keep going. I want trans kids to know they deserve love and support and to transition!

Tomorrow is TRANS DAY OF VISIBILITY 🏳️‍⚧️ Sierra and I will be going to DC to March and protest these bullshit laws. Come join us. Show us your support, we need it more than ever ❤️

Shirt: @grxyfit 

[IG: Chase taking a mirror selfie. They are wearing a black tshirt that says “trans kids deserve to grow”]

#TDOV #transgender #transrights #ftm #trans #transyouth #rights #femaletofedup

Today is International Transgender Day of Visibility, a day to celebrate and empower our beautiful transgender and non-binary selves! It is also a day to remind our allies to take action in our fight for our rights, especially given the unprecedented legislative and societal discrimination we are experiencing. Over 400 anti-trans bills have been introduced in at least 44 states. Public figures are openly calling for the eradication of trans people.

I’ve been transitioning for over 15 years now and I’m so tired of fighting to simply exist in this world. From the first day I realized I might be trans up to today, I haven’t stopped fighting. I just want people to recognize us as humans and let us live our lives! Gender affirming healthcare saved my life. Others should have the same opportunities ❤️🏳️‍⚧️

Swipe for a few things to do today, especially if you’re not transgender and would like to learn more about allyship.

#tdov #transdayofvisibility #allyshipisactive #eradicatetransphobia

13 YEARS ON T!! 🏳️‍⚧️

Obligatory trannaversary post hehe ✌🏼 

Every year that passes feels surreal. Realizing I was trans back in 2006, when I was 15, to finally starting hormones 💉 in 2010 (at 19), after years of internalized transphobia, acceptance, and then dealing with Quebec horrible system omg. But I did it :) I’m still here! I’m 32 now and WOW 👀 NEVER did I ever think I would make it to 30 🫣 Look at me go lol. Transitioning was the most amazing act of self love I have ever given myself and there is not one single day where I think “hmmmm should I have done that?” Nah ❤️❤️ Transitioning SAVES lives. 🏳️‍⚧️

Anyways, I get emotional every year when I go through ALL my photos so hiiii lol love me 👀

Also yes, hi, I’ve been taking my photo every. single. day. for 13 years ✌🏼

AC HALF IRONMAN RELAY 🏊🏼‍♂️

Not me getting called to sub in to the swim portion 2 HOURS before the race started. Other swimmer had an emergency and I stepped up! We thought this might happen to the night before we did have to dive home and back to AC (2 hours total lol) but it was worth it!

I was so nervous since I’ve never swam this distance. And this was the OCEAN-ish lol. But I did it! 1.2miles/1.9km in 47 minutes!!!!! For my first time, THATS A GREAT TIME! 

I got bopped in the face a couple of times during the swim but I was nice and calm. Last time I did a swim in that water, it was for TRI AC, 400m swim, no biggy. Well it was a biggie LOL. I had a panic attack and struggled through the whole thing. But NOT TODAY!!!! Today was so good. I paced myself and finished! And I’m so happy!

YAY!!!!!! Now I just have to train and do a half Ironman by myself lollllll 

Thanks to @caseylbohannon and @mxemdarcy for coming to cheer us on!!!

10 years sober! ❌🍺❌🎉

The road here has not been easy but it has been worth it. I’m a much better person than I was 10 years ago. I’ve done so much reflecting and so much work on myself throughout the years. Oddly enough it hasn’t gotten easier? I still have the urge to drink but I’m stronger than those thoughts. Also, those thoughts only come in when I’m stressed…. I know that a sober Chase can still be a FUN Chase! Thanks to everyone who has been there for me throughout the years. I wouldn’t have been able to get here without you ❤️
